Team Nigeria on Thursday defeated favourites,Â  Mauritius 3-2 to claim gold in the Mixed Team Championships at the All Africa Senior Badminton championships in Port Harcourt, Rivers State. The encounter went to the wire as both teams were tied at 2-2 heading the final game. The pair of Anuoluwapo Opeyori and Dorcas Adesokan defeated Julien Paul and Kune Foo 21-19, 21-19 in the mixed double to win the gold, confining Mauritius to second place. A jubilant Nigerian team celebrated the win the President of the Badminton Federation of Nigeria (BFN), Francis Orbih, who was excited by the win. The Singles will begin tomorrow and end on Sunday when the tournament will be declared closed.